V'''Barry Stroud''' (born 1935, [[Toronto]]) is a [[Canadians|Canadian]] philosopher known for his work on [[philosophical skepticism]], [[David Hume]], and [[Ludwig Wittgenstein]], among other topics. He received a B.A. in philosophy from the [[University of Toronto]], followed by a Ph.D. in philosophy from Harvard University, under the direction of [[Morton White]]. Since 1961, Stroud has worked at the [[University of California, Berkeley]]. In 1987, he gave the [[John Locke Lectures]] at [[Oxford University|Oxford]].<ref>http://www.philosophy.ox.ac.uk/lectures/john_locke_lectures/past_lectures</ref> In 2007 he was named Willis S. and Marion Slusser [[Professor]] of [[Philosophy]] in the Berkeley Philosophy Department.\u000a\u000aHe is an elected Fellow of the [[American Academy of Arts & Sciences]] and a Corresponding Fellow of the [[British Academy]].<ref>http://www.britac.ac.uk/fellowship/sections/index.cfm?member=2899</ref>\u000a\u000a==Selected works==\u000a* (1977) ''Hume''. [[Routledge]] (Winner of the Matchette Prize in 1979).\u000a* (1984) ''The Significance of Philosophical Scepticism''. [[Oxford University Press]]. ISBN 978-0-19-824761-6.\u000a* (1999) ''The Quest for Reality: Subjectivism & the Metaphysics of Colour''. Oxford University Press. ISBN 978-0-19-513388-2.\u000a* (2000) ''Understanding Human Knowledge: Philosophical Essays''. Oxford University Press. ISBN 978-0-19-825033-3.\u000a* (2000) "Meaning, Understanding, and Practice: Philosophical Essays". Oxford University Press. ISBN 978-0-19-825034-0.\u000a* (2011) "Engagement and Metaphysical Dissatisfaction: Modality and Value". Oxford University Press. ISBN 978-0-19-976496-9.\u000a* (2011) "Philosophers Past and Present: Selected Essays". Oxford University Press. ISBN 978-0-19-960859-1.\u000a\u000a==See also==\u000a*[[American philosophy]]\u000a*[[List of American philosophers]]\u000a\u000a==References==\u000a{{Reflist}}\u000a\u000a==External links==\u000a*[http://philosophy.berkeley.edu/stroud/ Faculty page at the University of Berkeley]\u000a*[http://www.tannerlectures.utah.edu/lectures/documents/stroud89.pdf The Study of Human Nature and the Subjectivity of Value], The [[Tanner Lectures on Human Values]]. Delivered at The University of Buenos Aires, June 7, 1988\u000a*[http://nigelwarburton.typepad.com/philosophy_bites/2007/12/barry-stroud-on.html Barry Stroud on Scepticism], podcast interview, December 16, 2007\u000a\u000a{{Authority control}}\u000a\u000a{{DEFAULTSORT:Stroud, Barry}}\u000a[[Category:Living people]]\u000a[[Category:Epistemologists]]\u000a[[Category:Fellows of the American Academy of Arts and Sciences]]\u000a[[Category:Fellows of the British Academy]]\u000a[[Category:Guggenheim Fellows]]\u000a[[Category:People from Toronto]]\u000a[[Category:University of Toronto alumni]]\u000a[[Category:Harvard University alumni]]\u000a[[Category:University of California, Berkeley faculty]]\u000a[[Category:American philosophers]]\u000a[[Category:Canadian philosophers]]\u000a[[Category:Wittgensteinian philosophers]]\u000a[[Category:1935 births]]\u000a\u000a\u000a{{US-philosopher-stub}}
